question.text: Which of the following is not the function of conducting part of respiratory system?

options.text: Temperature of inhaled air is brought to body temperature

Provides surface for diffusion of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>
It clears inhaled air from foreign particles

solution.text:
External nostrils to terminal bronchioles are called the conducting part of the respiratory system.

It serves the following functions

  • Transports the air to alveoli.
  • Clears foreign particles from the air.
  • Humidifies the incoming air.
  • Brings the air to body temperature.

Providing large surface area is not the function of the conducting part and is done by alveoli.
